<item>
            <title>[LU-4175] sanity test_180c: FAIL: error: test_brw: #3 - No space left on device on write</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4175</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While running sanity test 180c with default local configuration (OSTSIZE=200000), it failed as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 180c: test huge bulk I/O size on obdfilter, don&apos;t LASSERT == 01:03:30 (1383033810)
New object id is 0x2
getattr: object id 0x2
getattr: object id 2, mode 106666
error: test_brw: #3 - No space left on device on write
Print status every operation
test_brw: writing 10x16384 pages (obj 0x2, off 0): Tue Oct 29 01:03:30 2013
test_brw: write number 1 @ 2:0 for 67108864
test_brw: write number 2 @ 2:67108864 for 67108864
obecho_create_test failed: 4
ERROR: Module obdecho is in use
 sanity test_180c: @@@@@@ FAIL: test_180c failed with 4
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need fix obdecho_test() to calculate write count instead of hard-coding it with 10. I&apos;ll upload a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
